I've been long time holder of  brk.b and have no fears of the Oracle or Munger passing away. The company is fully prepared of both of their deaths and has been for a while;   

His will outlines no shares will be sold after his death but rather, over time, .a shares converted to .b shares which will be distributed to various foundations. He expects this will take 12-15 years so it won't be dramatic.  

The company has solid directors and managers that each control portions of the company, e.g. Todd Combs running a 14$ billion portion of their equity fund with Ted Weschler. These are some of the best of the best and it appears Buffet has full faith in them.
